Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
loadLefFile(25.10)                                          loadLefFile(25.10)

Name
       loadLefFile - Imports all the technology and library data that is spec-
       ified in the LEF files into the Innovus environment

Syntax
       loadLefFile

       [<file1 file2 ...>]<  >

       [-help]

       [-areaIo]

       [-blackbox]

       [-incremental]

       Imports  all  the  technology and library data that is specified in the
       LEF files into the Innovus environment. In addition, this command  pro-
       vides the location of the LEF files the routers need to access.

       You can use the loadLefFile command at any time.

       The  loadLefFile  command checks your LEF file to make sure that layers
       are defined in the correct order (as described in the LEF/DEF  Language
       Reference.)  For  example,  routing  layers must be defined alternately
       with cut layers:

       LAYER METAL1

       TYPE ROUTING

       END METAL1

       LAYER VIA12

       TYPE CUT

       END VIA12

       LAYER METAL2

       TYPE ROUTING

       END METAL2

       If you do not define layers in the correct order (for example,  if  you
       define  all routing layers before cut layers, the Innovus software dis-
       plays an error message.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each parameter of the loadLefFile command.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man loadLefFile.

       -areaIo
              Treats the pad macro cell as an areaIo cell. This option is used
              for versions of LEF prior to 5.5.

       -blackbox
              Treats  the  block macro cell as a blackbox. This option is used
              for versions of LEF prior to 5.5.

       <file1 file2 ...>
              Specify the names of LEF files to be loaded.

       -incremental
              Appends the antenna data into existing layers and  macro  cells.
              This is only used for appending LEF 5.4 antenna data.

Example
       The following command imports the LEF file technology data:

       loadLefFile sample.lef

